# automation-review-loop-unpushed-fix-oscillates — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-07-17)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus PR #2280 automation-loop containment
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Added containment for an out-of-scope address-agent draft that can survive agent SIGTERM through a retry or queued coordinator commit/push.
- Added remote-SHA-before-and-after containment workflow, including separate agent, coordinator, and push process checks.
- Added the rule to reset a disposable worktree only after all publishers stop and the remote is confirmed unchanged.

### Why

The existing recovery procedure handled a desired but unpushed fix. In PR #2280, the inverse occurred: an unwanted local draft was committed after its agent was stopped, and a push was already queued. The remote stayed safe only because the queued push was separately stopped.

